div.div:
NOTES:
THE DVWA MACHINES ARE CONFIGURED WITH FILEBEAT AND METRICBEAT SERVICES.
FILEBEAT ALLOWS FOR REAL TIME COLLECTION, STORAGE, AND VISUALIZATION OF SYSTEM LOGS.
METRICBEATS COLLECTS SYSTEM AND SERVICES' METRIC STATISTICS IN REALTIMETO MONITOR FOR IRREGULARITIES.
DVWA NETWORK SECURITY GROUP ONLY ACCEPTS THE HTTP CONNECTIONS FROM THE 'HOME' NETWORK FOR THE SECURITY.
OPTIONAL CONFIGURATIONS:
ALL OF THE MACHINES WITHIN THE ORGANIZATION RUN FILEBEAT AND METRICBEAT SERVICES.
THE ELK NSG IS SET TO ONLY ACCEPT HTTP CONNECTIONS FROM 'HOME' NETWORK AS WELL.
ELK LOAD BALANCER IS SET TO ACCEPT HTTP REQUESTS ON PORT 80 AND REDIRECT IT ON PORT 5601.
BOTH LOAD BALANCER PUBLIC FACING IP HAVE DNS RECORD ATTACHED TO THEM FOR CUSTOM DOMAIN USE.
THE BEAT CONFIGURATION AND SETUP IS MADE TO BE DONE THROUGH ANSIBLE PLAYBOOK.
JUMP BOX ACCEPT SSH CONNECTION FROM THE ANSIBLE CONTAINER IN ORDER TO RUN SYSTEM UPGRADE PLAYBOOK.
SYSTEM UPGRADE PLAYBOOK CAN BE SET AS A CHRON JOB TO FURTHER AUTOMATE THE TASK.
ANSIBLE HOSTS FILE CAN BE USED TO DEFENE RANGES OF THE IP ADDRESSES TO USE FOR PLAYBOOK
PLAYBOOK CAN BE SET TO DISCOVER HOSTS THAT ARE ONLINE BEFORE RUNNING MAIN TASKS
